### 6. **Navigation Back to Discover & Dev-Only Navigation**

**Routing back to discover:** Once US-038 (Discover feed) lands, the flow is:
- Tap card on `/feed` вҶ’ navigate `/(creator)/listing/[id]`
- Back-button вҶ’ pop to feed

**Until US-038 exists**, the temporary dev-link pattern:
```tsx
// Inside a dev component, gated by __DEV__ at the component level (Codebase Pattern #96)
if (__DEV__) {
  return (
    <View>
      <Button 
        label="Dev: Open listing detail"
        onPress={() => router.navigate('/(creator)/listing/d1a2b3c4-...')}
      />
    </View>
  );
}
```

**Key constraint:** Module-scope `const DEV_LISTING_ID = '...'` will NOT be tree-shaken even if wrapped in an `if (__DEV__)` branch вҖ” the const stays in the prod bundle. Instead, declare constants inside a dev-only component (Codebase Pattern #96), so the entire component + its closures get stripped together.

**Alternatively**, add a temporary deep-link route in `(creator)/_layout.tsx` that accepts a query param:
```tsx
// Temporary dev-only route added to (creator)/_layout.tsx
if (__DEV__ && route.name === 'listing-detail-dev') {
  return <ListingDetailScreen listingId={route.params?.id} />;
}
```

